      "id": "3237c98a9574b5b5",
      "text": "The narrative sequence in foprop goes like this:\n- The **weave architecture** - zones of reach, landscapes. The nature of practice, and theory of practice, and activist commitment.\n- The 'dance' of the **zones of reach**, in 'singing' patterns of very different kinds, into a practical frame of activist living\n- Care work - **In-here**; and the pattern families of care work\n- Subsistence work - **Here**: and the pattern families of subsistence work\n- Formación work - **We**: and the pattern families of formación work\n- Stewarding work - **Region**: and the pattern families of stewarding work\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "8d1380408d0c7c8d",
      "text": "These might be seen as segments of a 'cascade' of narrative, from the overall frame of commitment and insight (the weave), right down into the fine grain of the pattern-within-family (and its relationships - resonances across zones, affiliations within zones - with other patterns-within-families)."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "003402b269eaac93",
      "text": "**Segments of a cascade**\nPattern descriptions are needed not only for detailed patterns-within-families, but also for each segment is this narrative cascade:\n- The weave/project patterns [[We are engaged]] and [[Blessed unrest in the face of clear and present danger]]\n- The zones-of-reach pattern [[Beyond fragments - A fourfold dance]]\n*From here downwards, not currently developed*\n- Four families-within-this-zone patterns, for the four zones of reach\n- A whole bunch of patterns of patterns-within-this-family\n- Many individual, detail patterns, each at home in its family"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "c23fc831ea069ddf",
      "text": "> It probably helps to see this as an Alexandrian centres-and-wholes relationship, between weave/zone/family/pattern.\nHolmstad 2014, 'Fifteen properties of wholeness' [[Chris Alexander]]."
