        "text": "**Why 'foprop'?**\nIt's an acronym: **forces of production, relations of production**. There's more to be said about these historical concepts. But the point of foprop, as a pattern language of activist practice, is that the relations of production are **altered**, in contention with the hegemonic, over-arching, globalising social relations of 'the economy'."
